translated: Kjällgren, Yngve Martin, civil servant, doctor, Trollhättan, b. 26/6/1897 in Härja, Skaraborg. Firstborn of the clergyman Klas K. and Hedvig Kittel. Married in 1936 to Olga Bergström. Children: Ulla b. 1938, Christina b. 1941, Barbro b. 1943. - Completed secondary school in Skara 1916, earned a Bachelor's degree in medicine in Uppsala in 1922, and obtained a medical licensing there in 1928. Worked as a district physician in the Julita district from 1926 and in the Valla district from 1927, assistant doctor at the chest department in Uppsala and a doctor at Sätra spa in 1928, assistant doctor at the medical department of Vänersborg hospital from 1932, and had various appointments as a substitute and city doctor in Trollhättan. Also worked as a school doctor at Trollhättan's secondary school since 1934, and as a general practitioner in Trollhättan since 1929. Doctor for the primary school, telegraph, and railway.
